Package: simple-screen-capture
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Kerry Ritter <kerry@example.com>
Depends: maim, ffmpeg, xclip, optipng, openssl, curl,
 python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, libnotify-bin, x11-utils
Recommends: pulseaudio-utils
Description: Screenshot, GIF and screencast capture with an integrated GTK panel
 Trigger a full-screen capture panel via Ctrl+Shift+Alt+4 to:
  - Take area screenshots copied to clipboard as Image, Base64, or URL
  - Record area GIFs with palette-optimised colour
  - Record area screencasts as MP4 (with optional audio)
  - Upload captures to any S3-compatible host (AWS, R2, B2, MinIO)
    and copy the URL to clipboard instead of image bytes
 .
 Click-drag anywhere to redraw the region (like gnome-screenshot); drag
 inside to move; drag edges or corners to resize. The bottom toolbar
 holds mode tabs, contextual settings, and the capture/cancel buttons.
 Run `simple-screen-capture --setup` after install to wire up the
 keyboard shortcut and (optionally) configure S3/R2 upload.
